# State active project rules in the prompt response

On the **first substantive reply** of a new chat, fresh agent run, mode change, or topic switch—before any plan, explanation, or code—print exactly:

```markdown
### Active project rules
- `<subfolder>/<rule-name>.mdc`
- `<subfolder>/<rule-name>.mdc`
- ...
```

- One bullet per active rule file under `.cursor/rules/ai-rules/`. Skip `*.mdc.disabled`.
- Include any rule the user **@-mentioned** and any glob-scoped rule whose `globs` match the current files or task.
- Reprint when the user starts a new topic, switches mode (plan / build / test / role), or asks which rules apply. Skip on trivial tool-only follow-ups.
- One short sentence (≤ 20 words) acknowledging the request may appear before the heading—nothing else above it.
